# Design System — Use Tokens and Components, Never Custom Values

This project consumes the **Simple Design System** via CDN. Every color, spacing value, typography setting, shadow, radius, and UI component you need already exists. **Never create custom/hardcoded values** unless the user explicitly asks for something custom.

Full reference: https://starter-project-ds.netlify.app/

## Tokens (CSS custom properties from `tokens.css`)

### Colors — Always Use Semantic Tokens

Use **semantic** tokens (not primitives) so light/dark theming works automatically.

| Category | Examples |
|----------|---------|
| Background | `--bg-default`, `--bg-secondary`, `--bg-brand`, `--bg-positive`, `--bg-warning`, `--bg-danger`, plus `-hover`, `-secondary`, `-tertiary` variants |
| Text | `--text-default`, `--text-secondary`, `--text-tertiary`, `--text-brand`, `--text-positive`, `--text-warning`, `--text-danger`, plus `-on-*` variants for text on colored backgrounds |
| Border | `--border-default`, `--border-brand`, `--border-positive`, `--border-warning`, `--border-danger`, plus `-secondary`, `-tertiary` |
| Icon | `--icon-default`, `--icon-secondary`, `--icon-brand`, `--icon-positive`, `--icon-warning`, `--icon-danger`, plus `-on-*` variants |

Color primitives (`--brand-600`, `--gray-300`, etc.) should only be used if you need to define a new semantic token — never directly in component styles.

### Spacing

`--space-0` (0px), `--space-050` (2px), `--space-100` (4px), `--space-150` (6px), `--space-200` (8px), `--space-300` (12px), `--space-400` (16px), `--space-600` (24px), `--space-800` (32px), `--space-1200` (48px), `--space-1600` (64px), `--space-2400` (96px), `--space-4000` (160px)

Never write raw pixel values for spacing. Use these tokens.

### Typography

| Token | Value |
|-------|-------|
| `--text-title-hero` | 72px |
| `--text-title-page` | 48px |
| `--text-subtitle` | 32px |
| `--text-subtitle-small` | 24px |
| `--text-heading` | 24px |
| `--text-subheading` | 20px |
| `--text-body` | 16px |
| `--text-body-small` | 14px |

Weights: `--weight-regular` (400), `--weight-semibold` (600), `--weight-bold` (700)
Line heights: `--leading-tight` (1.2), `--leading-normal` (1.4), `--leading-none` (1), `--leading-code` (1.3)
Fonts: `--font-sans`, `--font-mono`

### Border Radius

`--radius-100` (4px), `--radius-200` (8px), `--radius-400` (16px), `--radius-full` (9999px)

### Shadows

Drop: `--shadow-100` through `--shadow-600`
Inner: `--inner-shadow-100` through `--inner-shadow-600`

### Stroke

`--stroke-border` (1px), `--stroke-focus-ring` (2px)

## Components — Use DS Classes

Before building any UI element, you **must** check the live DS reference to see if a component already exists.

### How to check for available components

1. **Fetch the live reference page** at https://starter-project-ds.netlify.app/ — this is the canonical source of truth for all available components, their class names, and usage examples.
2. **Fetch the live CSS** at https://starter-project-ds.netlify.app/css/components.css — this contains every component class the DS provides. Search it for relevant class names before creating anything custom.

Always do this lookup before writing new HTML. The DS is actively maintained and new components may be added at any time. Do not rely on a memorized list.

### Available token files (fetch these for the latest values)

- **Tokens:** https://starter-project-ds.netlify.app/css/tokens.css
- **Components:** https://starter-project-ds.netlify.app/css/components.css
- **Reset:** https://starter-project-ds.netlify.app/css/reset.css

## Rules

1. **Never hardcode colors.** No `#hex`, no `rgb()`, no `hsl()`. Always `var(--bg-*)`, `var(--text-*)`, `var(--border-*)`, `var(--icon-*)`.
2. **Never hardcode spacing.** No raw `px` for margin/padding/gap. Always `var(--space-*)`.
3. **Never hardcode font sizes.** Always `var(--text-*)` tokens.
4. **Never hardcode radii.** Always `var(--radius-*)`.
5. **Never hardcode shadows.** Always `var(--shadow-*)` or `var(--inner-shadow-*)`.
6. **Never invent components.** Check the DS reference first. Only create custom components when no DS equivalent exists AND the user has explicitly requested it.
7. **Project overrides go in `css/local.css`** and must still reference DS tokens.
8. **Icons** come from the CDN SVG sprite or the `icon()` JS helper.
